  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Champions of Purity pg. 30</em></p><p><strong>Aura</strong> strong abjuration and evocation [good] <strong>CL</strong> 12th</p><p><strong>Slot</strong> weapon quality; <strong>Price</strong> +3 bonus; <strong>Weight</strong> -</p><p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\"><strong>Description</strong></h3>A <em>redeemed </em>weapon was once a corrupt <em>unholy </em>weapon. The  taint of evil has been purged from it, however, and the weapon  is now in all ways a <em>holy </em>weapon, dealing an additional 2d6  points of damage against all creatures of evil alignment. In  addition, the wielder gains a sacred bonus on saving throws  equal to the weapon's enhancement bonus against the spells  and abilities of evil outsiders and a +5 competence bonus on  Knowledge (planes) checks to identify evil outsiders and their  special powers or vulnerabilities. When the <em>redeemed </em>weapon  special ability is added to an <em>unholy </em>weapon, the weapon loses  the <em>unholy </em>property and gains the <em>redeemed </em>property, and the  crafter must pay the price of adding a +1 enhancement bonus  to the weapon.</p><p><h3 class=\"framing\"><strong>Construction</strong></h3><strong>Requirements</strong> Craft Magic Arms and Armor, <em>consecrate</em>, <em>holy smite</em>, creator must be good; <strong>Price</strong> -</p>",
